pem243



Glasgow, Scotland





Level 6  Contributor 


141 reviews 


42 hotel reviews





55 helpful votes 





“Excellent facilities, room and service”


Reviewed March 21, 2012




It's no wonder that this place is rated number one and, similar to previous reviews, Jeff went out of his way to email us in advance, helping with eating & shopping locally, and upgrading us to a lovely big room. He seems to really care about his guests, despite the fact that we're very transient and I was impressed with the eco friendly products and recycling. We used the laundry which was much needed after about 10 days travelling and were able to walk to most places very easily. The visit was tinged with sadness at the devastation in Christchurch but there seems to be a huge amount of resilience in the people and hope for the future.





Stayed March 2012, traveled as a couple



Value



Location



Sleep Quality





Rooms



